{"title":"Robin Lovelace","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Robin Lovelace","description-meta":"Professor of Transport Data Science at University of Leeds","image":"files/profiles/profile1.JPG","page-navigation":false,"toc":false,"page-layout":"full","about":{"id":"hero-heading","template":"trestles","image-width":"70%","links":[{"icon":"envelope","text":"Email","href":"mailto:r.lovelace@leeds.ac.uk"},{"icon":"twitter","text":"Twitter","href":"https://twitter.com/robinlovelace","target":"_blank"},{"icon":"github","text":"GitHub","href":"https://github.com/robinlovelace","target":"_blank"},{"icon":"youtube","text":"YouTube","href":"https://www.youtube.com/c/RobinLovelace","target":"_blank"},{"icon":"mastodon","text":"Mastodon","href":"https://fosstodon.org/web/@robinlovelace","target":"_blank"},{"text":"{{< ai google-scholar >}} Google Scholar","href":"https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=xDJHVCAAAAAJ&hl=en","target":"_blank"}]},"listing":[{"id":"recent-posts","contents":["posts","posts/post-links.yml"],"exclude":{"title":""},"type":"grid","max-items":3,"page-size":3,"fields":["image","date","title","subtitle"],"max-description-length":100,"sort":["date desc"]}]},"headingText":"Research Interests","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n:::{#hero-heading}\n\nI'm a [Professor of Transport Data Science](https://environment.leeds.ac.uk/transport/staff/953/dr-robin-lovelace) at the [University of Leeds](https://www.leeds.ac.uk/) [Institute for Transport Studies](https://environment.leeds.ac.uk/transport)(ITS), where I undertake research, develop software and web applications, and teach data science for evidence-based transport planning.\n\n\n- **Geocomputation** - spatial data analysis and modeling\n- **Transport modelling** - active travel uptake and route modeling\n- **Reproducible research** - open source software and data-driven methods\n- **Decarbonising transport** - evidence-based planning for sustainable mobility\n\n## Current Projects\n\n- **SaferActive** - Improving safety for active travel through data-driven approaches\n- **Propensity to Cycle Tool (PCT)** - Online tool for cycling potential modeling\n- **Transport Data Science** - Teaching module for Masters students\n\n## Recent Work\n\nI share lots of code for data science and reproducible research. Check out my [GitHub](https://github.com/robinlovelace/) for projects and the [posts](/posts.qmd) section for blog entries.\n\nIf you'd like to get in touch, feel free to [email me](mailto:r.lovelace@leeds.ac.uk).\n\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":"\n\n:::{#hero-heading}\n\nI'm a [Professor of Transport Data Science](https://environment.leeds.ac.uk/transport/staff/953/dr-robin-lovelace) at the [University of Leeds](https://www.leeds.ac.uk/) [Institute for Transport Studies](https://environment.leeds.ac.uk/transport)(ITS), where I undertake research, develop software and web applications, and teach data science for evidence-based transport planning.\n\n## Research Interests\n\n- **Geocomputation** - spatial data analysis and modeling\n- **Transport modelling** - active travel uptake and route modeling\n- **Reproducible research** - open source software and data-driven methods\n- **Decarbonising transport** - evidence-based planning for sustainable mobility\n\n## Current Projects\n\n- **SaferActive** - Improving safety for active travel through data-driven approaches\n- **Propensity to Cycle Tool (PCT)** - Online tool for cycling potential modeling\n- **Transport Data Science** - Teaching module for Masters students\n\n## Recent Work\n\nI share lots of code for data science and reproducible research. Check out my [GitHub](https://github.com/robinlovelace/) for projects and the [posts](/posts.qmd) section for blog entries.\n\nIf you'd like to get in touch, feel free to [email me](mailto:r.lovelace@leeds.ac.uk).\n\n:::"},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","f